'''Alain Giresse''' (born [[August 2]], [[1952]] in [[Langoiran]], [[Gironde]]) was a [[France|French]] professional [[football (soccer)]] [[midfielder]]. He played for the [[France national football team]] in the [[1982 FIFA World Cup]] (fourth place) and the [[1986 FIFA World Cup]] (third place). He also was a member of the [[Euro 84]] winning team.

==Playing career==
* 1970-1986 : [[Girondins de Bordeaux]]
* 1986-1988 : [[Olympique de Marseille]]
* 582 matches in [[Ligue 1]], 164 goals
* 47 [[cap (football)|caps]], 6 goals

==Coaching career==
* 1995 - 1998 : [[Toulouse FC]]
* 1998 : [[Paris Saint-Germain]]
* 1999 - 2000 : [[Toulouse FC]]
* 2001 - 2003 : [[FAR Rabat]] (Morocco)
* 2004 - 2005 : [[Georgia national football team]]
* 2006 - : [[Gabon national football team]]

